'''South Londonderry''' was a [[United Kingdom constituencies|UK Parliament constituency]] in [[Ireland]]. It returned one [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) to the [[British House of Commons]] from [[1885]] until it was abolished in [[1922]].

==Boundaries and Boundary Changes==
This [[county constituency]] comprised the southern part of [[County Londonderry]].

Prior to the [[United Kingdom general election, 1885]] and after the dissolution of Parliament in 1922 the area was part of the [[Londonderry (UK Parliament constituency)|Londonderry]] constituency.

==Politics==
The constituency was a majority unionist area. 

All three candidates in 1918 were Catholics.  Had the [[Sinn F<U+00E9>in]] candidate won, then instead of taking up the Westminster seat he would have participated in the revolutionary [[First D<U+00E1>il]].

